<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="269" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[132,775,822,1039]" box="[132,222,822,848]" pageId="18" pageNumber="269">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[132,775,822,1039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="269">
Males of this species were only heard performing their characteristic lek-calling behaviour (
<bibRefCitation author="BRADBURY J. W." box="[475,640,885,911]" pageId="18" pageNumber="269" pagination="225 - 255" refId="ref17222" refString="BRADBURY J. W. 1977. - Lek mating behavior in the hammerheaded bat. Zeitschrift fur Tierpsychologie 45: 225 - 255. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0310.1977. tb 02120. x" type="journal article" year="1977">Bradbury 1977</bibRefCitation>
) in a nearby mango tree at Agumatsa Wildlife Sanctuary in 
<date box="[630,771,917,943]" pageId="18" pageNumber="269" value="2001-08">August 2001</date>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1861" box="[132,387,949,975]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Hypsignathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="269" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monstrosus">
<emphasis box="[132,387,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="269">Hypsignathus monstrosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been previously recorded in the 
<collectingRegion box="[132,275,980,1006]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="18" pageNumber="269">Volta Region</collectingRegion>
from Odomi Jongo, 
<quantity box="[513,592,980,1007]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.218688" pageId="18" pageNumber="269" unit="mi" value="2.0">2 miles</quantity>
E Nkwanta and Leklebi Agbesia (USNM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
